reviews.review_text: Sick show...... This was one of the most intense shows that I was at,Easter Sunday woo hoo !!! The group mind thing was in full effect,after Not Fade,everyone had the place shaking,then after the Quinn encore,the NFA reprise from the audience just kept going and going,the road crew was covering up everything and the crowd just kept stomping,clapping,and chanting NFA...Never seen the security so nervous about what was going on at any other show......Probably thought we were never gonna leave the building that nite!!!!!!

Boston Celtics in Attendance I was at this show and it rocked.  

Bill Walton and Larry Bird were in attendance and they rocked.

This is a great show and the sound is just fine!!!

show rocked I was at this show as well, and it absolutely did rock! Fairly long as well. First show I ever hitch hiked to. Love Providence. Gimme a good SBD, please....

Show's a five or so; sound's a two. If you were there, pick it up. Otherwise, wait for a better source...then get it!

"Easter 1986..." or that's what my tape says, anyways!  The end of this show is great--especially listen to pre-coma Garcia shred on Stella Blue and Bobby lead the band charging through Throwin Stones, leaving the crowd ready for the requisite NFA.  Classic 80's Dead!
Easter Sunday Dead I was at this show jerry wore red and I have Pictures to prove it. It was easter sunday.
Awesome! Stands out as one of my favs back east.  So many memories from this one

The crowd wouldn't leave!! So many shows, so many memories. After chatting with some friends recently about various shows and memories I remembered this show. Correction - I remembered Mighty Quinn for an encore and the crowd going completely wild for long after the band left the stage and EVEN after the lights came up - still deafening cheering. In ten years of seeing shows I had never seen anything like that. It took a while to remember the venue and year though! I don't necessarily remember the show being awesome (but it must have been) but I do remember the insane reaction and energy after the show. And, of course, I remember Why Don't We Do It In the Road.
